  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Humanitarian and Stabilization Support Towards Improved Human Security in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In this project, IOM aims to improve human security of migrants, internally displaced persons (IDPs) and communities of return in Somalia through the provision of integrated life-saving and stabilization support. In particular, IOM works on ensuring that affected populations have dignified, safe and secure living conditions with basic services through Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH), Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM), Health and Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) interventions. In addition, IOM provides returnees with medical and psychosocial support and livelihood assistance through individual and community rehabilitation projects.</narrative>
  </description>
